# Ken Project Setup Rule

This repository provides the `ken-project-setup` Skill. Treat `SKILL.md` as the source of truth.

## When To Apply

Apply this rule when the user asks to:

- initialize a Codex / AI project workspace,
- create `raw / docs / output / memory-bank / AGENTS.md / CLAUDE.md / .cursor/rules`,
- set up a Chinese office document project,
- prepare a project for Word, Excel, PPT, or PDF deliverables,
- add anti-hallucination or data-source rules to a project.

## Default Structure

Create or preserve this structure:

```text
<project>/
├─ AGENTS.md
├─ CLAUDE.md
├─ .cursor/rules/ken-project-setup.mdc
├─ raw/
├─ docs/
│  ├─ source-notes.md
│  └─ questions.md
├─ output/
└─ memory-bank/
   └─ PROJECT-MEMORY.md
```

## Preferred Command

Use the initializer script when possible:

```bash
python scripts/init_ken_project.py <target-directory>
```

Use `--force` only after explicit user confirmation.

## Safety Rules

- Preserve existing user files.
- Do not overwrite template files unless the user explicitly asks.
- Treat `raw/` as read-only original material.
- Put final Word, Excel, PPT, PDF, screenshots, and previews in `output/`.
- Put process notes, source notes, drafts, and open questions in `docs/`.
- Put durable, non-sensitive project context in `memory-bank/`.
- Generate `CLAUDE.md` for Claude Code compatibility.
- Generate `.cursor/rules/ken-project-setup.mdc` for Cursor compatibility.
- Never store secrets, API keys, passwords, credentials, or private customer data in `memory-bank/`.

## Data And Fact Rules

- Prefer facts and data from `raw/`, `docs/`, and `memory-bank/`.
- External sources must include source name, link or file name, and citation date.
- Do not fabricate customers, amounts, growth rates, market data, citations, or conclusions.
- If information is missing, write it to `docs/questions.md` instead of guessing.
- Key data in Word, Excel, PPT, and PDF outputs must cite its source.

## Office Skill Routing

- Word / DOCX: use `minimax-docx`.
- Excel / XLSX: use `minimax-xlsx`.
- PPT / PPTX: use `ppt-master`.
- Formal PDF reports: use `minimax-pdf`.

## Validation

After editing this repository:

```bash
python -m py_compile scripts/init_ken_project.py
```

If available, also run the Skill validator:

```bash
python <skill-creator>/scripts/quick_validate.py .
```
